## MADSci Patterns

- Actions are defined with the `@action` decorator in the REST node class
- Interface classes are independent of MADSci and can be used standalone (in scripts, notebooks, etc.)
- Configuration uses Pydantic models; settings come from environment variables or config files
- The fake interface mirrors the real interface's API for hardware-free development and testing
- Drivers in `src/drivers/` can contain vendor-specific code; use `src/drivers/private/` for proprietary code

